  "title": "Deploying Web Backends Using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide provides a comprehensive overview of how to deploy web backends using FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.12+.",

  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI supports automatic documentation, type hints, and makes it easier to write secure and maintainable APIs.",
    "It integrates seamlessly with a variety of tools such as SQLAlchemy for database connectivity, Uvicorn or Hypercube for deployment, and Swagger UI for API documentation.",
    "FastAPI is designed with an emphasis on developer ergonomics, allowing you to focus on writing your application logic rather than boilerplate code.",
  ],

